HEADWORD: lido
<hw>lido</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <ety>[After the <ets>Lido</ets>,
a group of sandy barrier islands between the lagoon of Venice and the
Adriatic, a popular beach resort.]</ety> <def>A recreational facility,
especially one including a swimming pool for water sports.</def>
<mark>[British]</mark> ⟦br⟧
